{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870091600,"sessionID":"ses_285e55f5dffegp5DkG1YGAfjh5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1b1de7001n6SKZl5kmgHv0m","messageID":"msg_d7a1b047d0016C3zm5U3Wea3WJ","sessionID":"ses_285e55f5dffegp5DkG1YGAfjh5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-015c8c86b4ce4aaeadacdf9fdf552948","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-021 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Implement the `build` command in AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces. The command orchestrates the entire build lifecycle: validating prerequisites, incrementing version metadata, building via Docker SDK or cloud provider, and updating metadata with build results.\n17: \n18: **Current State**: CLI has `pack` command that generates Dockerfile and packages workspace, but no build capability. Users must manually run `docker build` after packaging.\n19: \n20: **Target State**: \n21: - Single `kubectl-agentcube build` command that builds container image from packaged workspace\n22: - Automatic version increment (patch bump) before build with rollback on failure\n23: - Support for local Docker build mode (cloud mode placeholder)\n24: - Metadata updated with image info, build time, and image ID\n25: - Proxy support for dependency resolution\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 In Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` class with build orchestration logic |\n36: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | `build` Typer command with CLI options |\n37: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` for Docker SDK integration (build, push, remove) |\n38: \n39: ### 2.2 BuildRuntime Methods\n40: \n41: | Method | Purpose |\n42: |--------|---------|\n43: | `build(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n44: | `_increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)` | Patch bump version (X.Y.Z → X.Y.Z+1) or append .1 |\n45: | `_validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)` | Check Docker availability, Dockerfile existence |\n46: | `_build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Local Docker build via SDK |\n47: | `_build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Cloud build (placeholder for future) |\n48: | `_update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, build_result, tag)` | Persist image info to metadata YAML |\n49: \n50: ### 2.3 CLI Options\n51: \n52: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n53: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n54: | `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n55: | `--proxy` / `-p` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n56: | `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n57: | `--output` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for build artifacts |\n58: | `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n59: \n60: ### 2.4 Out of Scope\n61: \n62: | Item | Reason |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Cloud build implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n65: | Multi-architecture builds | Not specified in requirements; future enhancement |\n66: | Build cache optimization | Docker SDK handles caching internally |\n67: | Image vulnerability scanning | Separate security concern |\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n72: \n73: ### 3.1 新增文件\n74: \n75: ```\n76: cmd/cli/\n77: ├── agentcube/\n78: │   ├── runtime/\n79: │   │   └── build_runtime.py      # BuildRuntime class\n80: │   ├── services/\n81: │   │   └── docker_service.py     # DockerService class\n82: │   └── cli/\n83: │   │   └── main.py               # build command (addition to existing)\n84: │   └── models/\n85: │   │   └── pack_models.py        # MetadataOptions (shared with pack)\n86: └── tests/\n87:     └── test_build_runtime.py     # Unit tests for BuildRuntime\n88:     └── test_docker_service.py    # Unit tests for DockerService\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n92: \n93: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n94: |------------|---------|--------|\n95: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; required for local build |\n96: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n97: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and status output |\n98: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n99: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Version bump logic |\n100: \n101: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n102: \n103: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n104: |----------|--------------|\n105: | `publish` command | Uses built image name/tag from metadata |\n106: | `status` command | Reads image info from metadata |\n107: | `pack` command | Provides Dockerfile path for build |\n108: | Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent` |\n109: \n110: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n111: \n112: - **Metadata schema**: Adding `image` field with sub-fields (`image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`, `tag`) to `AgentMetadata`\n113: - **Version field**: Build modifies `metadata.version` in-place; concurrent builds could conflict\n114: - **Dockerfile location**: Build expects `Dockerfile` at workspace root (generated by `pack`)\n115: \n116: ### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n117: \n118: - Docker SDK `docker.from_env()` requires Docker daemon running\n119: - Version increment follows semver pattern: `X.Y.Z` → `X.Y.(Z+1)`\n120: - Non-semver versions: append `.1` (e.g., `v1.0` → `v1.0.1`)\n121: - Empty version: fallback to `{version}-1` or generate timestamp-based tag\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n126: \n127: ### Alternative 1: Shell Command Execution\n128: \n129: **Approach**: Execute `docker build` via `subprocess.run()` instead of Docker SDK.\n130: \n131: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n132: |--------|------------|\n133: | Pros | Simpler implementation; no SDK dependency |\n134: | Cons | No structured output parsing; harder error handling; no image info extraction; platform-specific quirks |\n135: \n136: **Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK provides structured image info (image_id, size) and cleaner exception handling.\n137: \n138: ### Alternative 2: Kaniko for Rootless Builds\n139: \n140: **Approach**: Use Kaniko executor for builds without Docker daemon.\n141: \n142: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n143: |--------|------------|\n144: | Pros | No Docker daemon required; CI-friendly; rootless |\n145: | Cons | Additional dependency; requires Kubernetes environment; not suitable for local dev workflow |\n146: \n147: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as optional build backend for cloud mode.\n148: \n149: ### Alternative 3: Buildah/Podman\n150: \n151: **Approach**: Support Buildah or Podman as alternative container build tools.\n152: \n153: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n154: |--------|------------|\n155: | Pros | Daemonless; OCI-compliant; rootless option |\n156: | Cons | Different CLI interface; less Python SDK support; broader compatibility testing needed |\n157: \n158: **Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK covers primary use case; Podman support could be future extension.\n159: \n160: ### Alternative 4: Manual Version Management\n161: \n162: **Approach**: Require user to specify version via `--version` flag instead of auto-increment.\n163: \n164: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n165: |--------|------------|\n166: | Pros | Explicit control; no rollback complexity |\n167: | Cons | Manual burden; potential duplicate tags; workflow friction |\n168: \n169: **Decision**: Rejected. Auto-increment with rollback on failure provides safer workflow per spec requirements.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## 5. Risks\n174: \n175: | Risk | Mitigation |\n176: |------|------------|\n177: | Docker daemon unavailable | `_validate_build_prerequisites` checks `DockerService.check_docker_available()` before build |\n178: | Version rollback race condition | Build modifies metadata file; use atomic write pattern |\n179: | Build timeout on large images | Docker SDK streaming build; no explicit timeout in spec |\n180: | Registry auth for push (future) | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles auth when credentials provided |\n181: | Image name collision | Use `{agent_name}:{version}` pattern; sanitize agent_name |\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n186: \n187: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.check_docker_available()` with `docker.from_env()` try/catch\n188: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.build_image()` with streaming logs, build_args for proxy\n189: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.get_image_info()` for image_id, size extraction\n190: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.push_image()` with optional registry auth\n191: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.remove_image()` with graceful failure handling\n192: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` with semver logic\n193: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` for Docker + Dockerfile check\n194: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._build_local()` orchestrating Docker build\n195: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()` persisting results\n196: - [ ] Add `build` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n197: - [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n198: - [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for build status\n199: - [ ] Add `image` field to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n200: - [ ] Unit tests for version increment edge cases\n201: - [ ] Unit tests for Docker unavailable scenarios\n202: - [ ] Integration test for full build workflow\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## 7. References\n207: \n208: - Spec: `changes/AR-021/spec.md`\n209: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n210: - CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: `build` command\n211: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n212: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n213: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 213 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-021 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `build` command in AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces. The command orchestrates the entire build lifecycle: validating prerequisites, incrementing version metadata, building via Docker SDK or cloud provider, and updating metadata with build results.\n\n**Current State**: CLI has `pack` command that generates Dockerfile and packages workspace, but no build capability. Users must manually run `docker build` after packaging.\n\n**Target State**: ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870091587,"end":1775870091598}}}}
