{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870238171,"sessionID":"ses_285e55f5dffegp5DkG1YGAfjh5","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1d5d3d001Hg4cNmsSQeJpsK","messageID":"msg_d7a1b218c001K28bmx0tU8tqAt","sessionID":"ses_285e55f5dffegp5DkG1YGAfjh5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-a218ef27c4854680a88a3344268e2f8b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md","content":"# AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nBuild command for AgentCube CLI that constructs container images from packaged agent workspaces. Orchestrates the full build lifecycle: prerequisite validation, version increment, Docker SDK build execution, and metadata persistence.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        User Environment                          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│   ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐    │\n│   │ Agent        │     │ agent_       │     │ Dockerfile   │    │\n│   │ Workspace    │────▶│ metadata.    │────▶│ (generated   │    │\n│   │ (./my-agent) │     │ yaml         │     │ by pack)     │    │\n│   └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘    │\n│          │                   │                    │              │\n│          └───────────────────┴────────────────────┘              │\n│                              │                                   │\n│                              ▼                                   │\n│                    ┌──────────────────┐                          │\n│                    │ kubectl-agentcube│                          │\n│                    │     build -f .   │                          │\n│                    └──────────────────┘                          │\n│                              │                                   │\n└──────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     AgentCube CLI                                │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│   │                  CLI Layer (main.py)                     │   │\n│   │  ┌─────────┐                                             │   │\n│   │  │ build() │  Typer command handler                      │   │\n│   │  │         │  - Parse options                            │   │\n│   │  │         │  - Rich Progress spinner                    │   │\n│   │  │         │  - Error handling via _handle_error         │   │\n│   │  └─────────┘                                             │   │\n│   └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                           │                                      │\n│                           ▼                                      │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│   │                Runtime Layer                             │   │\n│   │  ┌──────────────┐                                        │   │\n│   │  │ BuildRuntime │  Orchestration class                   │   │\n│   │  │              │  - build() main entry                  │   │\n│   │  │              │  - _increment_version()                │   │\n│   │  │              │  - _validate_build_prerequisites()    │   │\n│   │  │              │  - _build_local() / _build_cloud()    │   │\n│   │  │              │  - _update_build_metadata()           │   │\n│   │  └──────────────┘                                        │   │\n│   └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                           │                                      │\n│                           ▼                                      │\n│   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│   │                Service Layer                             │   │\n│   │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐                     │   │\n│   │  │ DockerService│  │MetadataService│                    │   │\n│   │  │              │  │               │                     │   │\n│   │  │ - check_     │  │ - load_       │                     │   │\n│   │  │   docker_    │  │   metadata()  │                     │   │\n│   │  │   available()│  │ - save_       │                     │   │\n│   │  │ - build_     │  │   metadata()  │                     │   │\n│   │  │   image()    │  │               │                     │   │\n│   │  │ - get_       │  │               │                     │   │\n│   │  │   image_     │  │               │                     │   │\n│   │  │   info()     │  │               │                     │   │\n│   │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘                     │   │\n│   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                  │\n└───────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┘\n                                │\n                                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     External Systems                             │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│   ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐                    │\n│   │ Docker       │          │ Metadata     │                    │\n│   │ Daemon       │◀────────▶│ YAML File    │                    │\n│   │ (dockerd)    │          │ (workspace)  │                    │\n│   └──────────────┘          └──────────────┘                    │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         agentcube/runtime/                          │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                     │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                    BuildRuntime                               │  │\n│  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  │\n│  │ Fields:                                                       │  │\n│  │   - verbose: bool                                             │  │\n│  │   - docker_service: DockerService                             │  │\n│  │   - metadata_service: MetadataService                         │  │\n│  │                                                               │  │\n│  │ Methods:                                                      │  │\n│  │   + build(workspace_path: Path, **options) → Dict[str, Any]   │  │\n│  │   + _increment_version(workspace_path, metadata) → str       │  │\n│  │   + _validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path) → None     │  │\n│  │   + _build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options) → Dict   │  │\n│  │   + _build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options) → Dict   │  │\n│  │   + _update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata,         │  │\n│  │                           build_result, tag) → None           │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                                                                     │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         agentcube/services/                        │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                     │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │       DockerService        │  │      MetadataService       │    │\n│  ├────────────────────────────┤  ├────────────────────────────┤    │\n│  │ Fields:                    │  │ Fields:                    │    │\n│  │   - verbose: bool          │  │   - verbose: bool          │    │\n│  │   - client: DockerClient   │  │                            │    │\n│  │                            │  │ Methods:                   │    │\n│  │ Methods:                   │  │   + load_metadata()        │    │\n│  │   + check_docker_available│  │   + save_metadata()        │    │\n│  │   + build_image()          │  │   + update_metadata()      │    │\n│  │   + get_image_info()       │  │                            │    │\n│  │   + push_image()           │  │                            │    │\n│  │   + remove_image()         │  │                            │    │\n│  └────────────────────────────┘  └────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                                                                     │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nUser Input: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --verbose\n\n                ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                │  CLI Entry (main.py)                    │\n                │                                         │\n                │  1. Parse Typer options                 │\n                │     - workspace: str                    │\n                │     - proxy: Optional[str]              │\n                │     - cloud_provider: Optional[str]     │\n                │     - output: Optional[str]             │\n                │     - verbose: bool                     │\n                │                                         │\n                │  2. Initialize BuildRuntime(verbose)    │\n                │                                         │\n                │  3. Start Rich Progress spinner         │\n                │                                         │\n                │  4. Call runtime.build(workspace, ...)  │\n                └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n                                 │\n                                 ▼\n                ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                │  BuildRuntime.build()                   │\n                │                                         │\n                │  Step 1: Load metadata                  │\n                │     metadata_service.load_metadata()    │\n                │     → AgentMetadata                     │\n                │                                         │\n                │  Step 2: Validate prerequisites         │\n                │     _validate_build_prerequisites()     │\n                │     - Check Docker available            │\n                │     - Check Dockerfile exists           │\n                │                                         │\n                │  Step 3: Increment version              │\n                │     original_version = metadata.version │\n                │     new_tag = _increment_version()      │\n                │     - X.Y.Z → X.Y.(Z+1)                 │\n                │     - v1.0 → v1.0.1                     │\n                │     - None → \"latest\"                   │\n                │                                         │\n                │  Step 4: Execute build                  │\n                │     if build_mode == \"local\":           │\n                │         result = _build_local()         │\n                │     else:                               │\n                │         result = _build_cloud()         │\n                │                                         │\n                │  Step 5: Handle result                  │\n                │     if success:                         │\n                │         _update_build_metadata()        │\n                │         return result                   │\n                │     if failure:                         │\n                │         rollback version to original    │\n                │         raise RuntimeError              │\n                └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n                                 │\n                                 ▼\n                ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                │  BuildRuntime._build_local()            │\n                │                                         │\n                │  1. Resolve image name                  │\n                │     image_name = f\"{agent_name}:{tag}\"  │\n                │                                         │\n                │  2. Build with Docker SDK               │\n                │     docker_service.build_image(         │\n                │         dockerfile_path=workspace/      │\n                │                       Dockerfile,       │\n                │         context_path=workspace,         │\n                │         image_name=image_name,          │\n                │         tag=tag,                        │\n                │         build_args={                    │\n                │             \"PROXY\": proxy              │\n                │         } if proxy else None            │\n                │     )                                   │\n                │                                         │\n                │  3. Get image info                      │\n                │     docker_service.get_image_info()     │\n                │     → image_id, image_size              │\n                │                                         │\n                │  4. Return build result dict            │\n                │     {                                   │\n                │         \"image_name\": \"...\",            │\n                │         \"image_id\": \"...\",              │\n                │         \"image_size\": \"...\",            │\n                │         \"build_time\": \"...\",            │\n                │         \"tag\": tag                      │\n                │     }                                   │\n                └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n                                 │\n                                 ▼\n                ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                │  DockerService.build_image()            │\n                │                                         │\n                │  1. Get Docker client                   │\n                │     client = docker.from_env()          │\n                │                                         │\n                │  2. Build image with streaming          │\n                │     for line in client.api.build(       │\n                │         path=str(context_path),         │\n                │         dockerfile=str(dockerfile),     │\n                │         tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",      │\n                │         buildargs=build_args,           │\n                │         decode=True                     │\n                │     ):                                  │\n                │         if verbose: log each line      │\n                │                                         │\n                │  3. Measure build time                  │\n                │     start_time → end_time               │\n                │                                         │\n                │  4. Return structured result            │\n                └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n                                 │\n                                 ▼\n                ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                │  CLI Output                             │\n                │                                         │\n                │  Success:                               │\n                │    [green] Build completed successfully │\n                │    Image: {image_name}:{tag}            │\n                │    Image ID: {image_id}                 │\n                │    Size: {image_size}                   │\n                │    Build time: {build_time}s            │\n                │                                         │\n                │  Failure:                               │\n                │    [red] Error build: {error}           │\n                │    [if verbose] Full traceback          │\n                │    Exit code: 1                         │\n                └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\nBuild command modifies and reads these fields:\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    agent_name: str                      # Used for image name\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    language: str = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: str                      # Dockerfile ENTRYPOINT\n    port: int = 8080                     # Dockerfile EXPOSE\n    build_mode: str = \"local\"            # \"local\" or \"cloud\"\n    region: Optional[str] = None\n    version: Optional[str] = None        # Incremented on build\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None  # Updated with build result\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = None\n    session_id: Optional[str] = None\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n\n    @field_validator(\"language\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n        if v.lower() not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n        if v.lower() not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n        return v.lower()\n\n    @field_validator(\"port\")\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n        if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n            raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n        return v\n```\n\n### image Field Structure\n\n```python\nimage: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = {\n    \"image_name\": str,       # e.g., \"my-agent\"\n    \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (sha256:...)\n    \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n    \"build_time\": float,     # Build duration in seconds\n    \"tag\": str,              # Image tag (e.g., \"v1.0.1\" or \"latest\")\n}\n```\n\n### BuildResult (Internal)\n\n```python\nBuildResult = Dict[str, Any] = {\n    \"image_name\": str,\n    \"image_id\": str,\n    \"image_size\": str,\n    \"build_time\": float,\n    \"tag\": str,\n    \"success\": bool,\n    \"error\": Optional[str],\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Command Interface\n\n| Command | Arguments | Description |\n|---------|-----------|-------------|\n| `build` | `--workspace` `-f` | Path to agent workspace directory (default: `.`) |\n| `build` | `--proxy` `-p` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n| `build` | `--cloud-provider` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `build` | `--output` | Output path for build artifacts |\n| `build` | `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### Typer Command Signature\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef build(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\n        \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\",\n        help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n        show_default=True\n    ),\n    proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\",\n        help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"\n    ),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n        help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n    ),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--output\",\n        help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"\n    ),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n        False, \"--verbose\",\n        help=\"Enable detailed logging\"\n    ),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Build a container image from a packaged agent workspace.\"\"\"\n    workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n    \n    with Progress(\n        SpinnerColumn(),\n        TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n        console=console,\n    ) as progress:\n        task = progress.add_task(\"Building agent image...\", total=None)\n        \n        try:\n            runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n            result = runtime.build(\n                workspace_path,\n                proxy=proxy,\n                cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n                output=output,\n            )\n            progress.update(task, description=\"Build completed\")\n            \n            console.print(f\"[green]Build completed successfully[/green]\")\n            console.print(f\"Image: {result['image_name']}:{result['tag']}\")\n            console.print(f\"Image ID: {result['image_id']}\")\n            console.print(f\"Size: {result['image_size']}\")\n            console.print(f\"Build time: {result['build_time']}s\")\n            \n        except Exception as e:\n            progress.stop()\n            _handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)\n```\n\n### BuildRuntime.build() Contract\n\n```python\ndef build(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    **options: Any,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build container image from workspace.\n    \n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n        options: Build options including:\n            - proxy: Optional[str] - Proxy URL for build args\n            - cloud_provider: Optional[str] - Cloud provider name\n            - output: Optional[str] - Output path\n    \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n            - image_name: str\n            - image_id: str\n            - image_size: str\n            - build_time: float\n            - tag: str\n    \n    Raises:\n        RuntimeError: If Docker is not available\n        ValueError: If Dockerfile does not exist\n        RuntimeError: If build fails (version rolled back)\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### DockerService.build_image() Contract\n\n```python\ndef build_image(\n    self,\n    dockerfile_path: Path,\n    context_path: Path,\n    image_name: str,\n    tag: str = \"latest\",\n    build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build Docker image using Docker SDK.\n    \n    Args:\n        dockerfile_path: Path to Dockerfile\n        context_path: Build context directory\n        image_name: Image name without tag\n        tag: Image tag\n        build_args: Optional build arguments (e.g., {\"PROXY\": url})\n    \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n            - image_name: str (name:tag)\n            - image_id: str (sha256 digest)\n            - image_size: str (human-readable)\n            - build_time: float (seconds)\n    \n    Raises:\n        docker.errors.BuildError: If build fails\n        docker.errors.APIError: If Docker API error\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Category | Condition | Action |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| Docker Unavailable | `docker.from_env()` fails | Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` |\n| Missing Dockerfile | No `Dockerfile` in workspace | Raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")` |\n| Build Failure | Docker build returns error | Rollback version, raise `RuntimeError` |\n| Invalid Metadata | Pydantic validation fails | Propagate `ValidationError` |\n| Version Rollback | Build fails after increment | Restore original version in metadata file |\n\n### _handle_error() Pattern\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Unified error handler for CLI commands.\n    \n    Prints error message in red, optionally shows traceback,\n    and exits with code 1.\n    \"\"\"\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### Version Rollback Logic\n\n```python\ndef _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Increment version with rollback capability.\n    \n    Returns new tag; caller must rollback on failure.\n    \"\"\"\n    original_version = metadata.version\n    try:\n        # Increment logic\n        if metadata.version:\n            if semver.VersionInfo.isvalid(metadata.version):\n                v = semver.VersionInfo.parse(metadata.version)\n                new_version = str(v.bump_patch())\n            elif metadata.version.startswith(\"v\"):\n                # v1.0 → v1.0.1\n                base = metadata.version[1:]\n                new_version = f\"v{base}.1\"\n            else:\n                # Fallback: append -1\n                new_version = f\"{metadata.version}-1\"\n        else:\n            new_version = \"latest\"\n        \n        metadata.version = new_version\n        self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n        return new_version\n        \n    except Exception:\n        metadata.version = original_version\n        raise\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test File | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `tests/test_build_runtime.py` | BuildRuntime methods |\n| `tests/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService methods |\n| `tests/test_version_increment.py` | Version bump edge cases |\n\n### Test Cases\n\n#### BuildRuntime Tests\n\n```python\nclass TestBuildRuntime:\n    def test_build_local_success(self, mock_docker_service, mock_metadata):\n        \"\"\"Successful local build returns image info.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_build_docker_unavailable(self, mock_docker_unavailable):\n        \"\"\"Raises RuntimeError when Docker not running.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_build_missing_dockerfile(self, workspace_no_dockerfile):\n        \"\"\"Raises ValueError when Dockerfile missing.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_version_increment_semver(self):\n        \"\"\"X.Y.Z → X.Y.(Z+1) for valid semver.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_version_increment_v_prefix(self):\n        \"\"\"v1.0 → v1.0.1 for v-prefixed versions.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_version_increment_fallback(self):\n        \"\"\"custom → custom-1 for non-semver strings.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_version_rollback_on_failure(self, mock_build_failure):\n        \"\"\"Original version restored when build fails.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_build_cloud_placeholder(self):\n        \"\"\"Cloud build returns placeholder dict.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### DockerService Tests\n\n```python\nclass TestDockerService:\n    def test_check_docker_available_running(self, mock_docker_client):\n        \"\"\"Returns True when Docker daemon running.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_check_docker_available_not_running(self):\n        \"\"\"Returns False when Docker daemon unavailable.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_build_image_success(self, mock_docker_api):\n        \"\"\"build_image returns image info dict.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_build_image_with_proxy(self, mock_docker_api):\n        \"\"\"Proxy passed as build_arg.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_get_image_info(self, mock_image):\n        \"\"\"Extracts image_id and size.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_push_image_with_auth(self, mock_registry):\n        \"\"\"Login and push with credentials.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_remove_image_success(self, mock_image):\n        \"\"\"Returns True on removal.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_remove_image_failure(self):\n        \"\"\"Returns False, logs warning.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\nclass TestBuildIntegration:\n    def test_full_build_workflow(self, packaged_workspace):\n        \"\"\"End-to-end: validate → increment → build → update metadata.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_build_after_pack(self, agent_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Pack creates Dockerfile, build succeeds.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_rebuild_increments_version(self, built_workspace):\n        \"\"\"Second build bumps version again.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_docker_service():\n    \"\"\"Mock DockerService with fake client.\"\"\"\n    \n@pytest.fixture\ndef packaged_workspace(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Temporary workspace with Dockerfile and metadata.\"\"\"\n    \n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_build_failure():\n    \"\"\"Mock Docker SDK to raise BuildError.\"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── main.py              # build command addition\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── pack_models.py       # MetadataOptions (shared)\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py      # Existing\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py     # NEW: BuildRuntime\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py   # Future\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py    # Future\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py    # Future\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py  # Existing\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py    # NEW: DockerService\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py      # Future\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py # Future\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py\n├── examples/\n│   ├── hello-agent/\n│   │   └── main.py\n│   └── math-agent/\n│       └── main.py\n└── tests/\n    ├── __init__.py\n    ├── test_pack_runtime.py      # Existing\n    ├── test_build_runtime.py     # NEW\n    ├── test_docker_service.py    # NEW\n    └── test_version_increment.py # NEW\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; local build execution |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file I/O |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, console output |\n| `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic version parsing and bumping |\n| `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n\n### Dev Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `pytest` | `>=7.4.0` | Test framework |\n| `pytest-asyncio` | `>=0.21.0` | Async test support |\n| `pytest-cov` | `>=4.1.0` | Coverage reporting |\n| `pytest-mock` | `>=3.11.0` | Mocking fixtures |\n| `ruff` | `>=0.1.0` | Linting |\n| `mypy` | `>=1.5.0` | Type checking |\n\n### Optional Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | K8s client (for publish command) |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Version Increment Strategy\n\n```python\ndef _increment_version(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Semver bump strategy:\n    \n    1. Valid semver (X.Y.Z): bump_patch → X.Y.(Z+1)\n       Example: 1.2.3 → 1.2.4\n    \n    2. v-prefixed non-semver (vX.Y): append .1\n       Example: v1.0 → v1.0.1\n    \n    3. Non-semver string: append -1\n       Example: custom → custom-1\n    \n    4. None/empty: use \"latest\"\n    \"\"\"\n    import semver\n    \n    if not metadata.version:\n        return \"latest\"\n    \n    version_str = metadata.version\n    \n    if semver.VersionInfo.isvalid(version_str.lstrip(\"v\")):\n        base = version_str.lstrip(\"v\")\n        v = semver.VersionInfo.parse(base)\n        new_v = v.bump_patch()\n        prefix = \"v\" if version_str.startswith(\"v\") else \"\"\n        return f\"{prefix}{new_v}\"\n    \n    if version_str.startswith(\"v\") and \".\" in version_str:\n        return f\"{version_str}.1\"\n    \n    return f\"{version_str}-1\"\n```\n\n### Docker Build Streaming\n\n```python\ndef build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, \n                image_name: str, tag: str, build_args: Optional[Dict]) -> Dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Stream build logs for verbose output:\n    \"\"\"\n    import docker\n    import time\n    \n    client = docker.from_env()\n    full_tag = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n    start_time = time.time()\n    \n    build_kwargs = {\n        \"path\": str(context_path),\n        \"dockerfile\": str(dockerfile_path),\n        \"tag\": full_tag,\n        \"buildargs\": build_args,\n        \"decode\": True,\n    }\n    \n    for line in client.api.build(**build_kwargs):\n        if self.verbose and \"stream\" in line:\n            print(line[\"stream\"].strip())\n        if \"error\" in line:\n            raise docker.errors.BuildError(line[\"error\"], build_log)\n    \n    build_time = time.time() - start_time\n    \n    image = client.images.get(full_tag)\n    return {\n        \"image_name\": image_name,\n        \"image_id\": image.id,\n        \"image_size\": self._format_size(image.attrs[\"Size\"]),\n        \"build_time\": round(build_time, 2),\n        \"tag\": tag,\n    }\n```\n\n### Proxy Build Arg\n\n```python\ndef _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, \n                 options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Proxy handling:\n    \"\"\"\n    build_args = None\n    if options.get(\"proxy\"):\n        build_args = {\"PROXY\": options[\"proxy\"]}\n    \n    dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n    \n    return self.docker_service.build_image(\n        dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n        context_path=workspace_path,\n        image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n        tag=options.get(\"tag\", metadata.version or \"latest\"),\n        build_args=build_args,\n    )\n```\n\n### Metadata Update Pattern\n\n```python\ndef _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata,\n                           build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Update metadata.image with build result:\n    \"\"\"\n    metadata.image = {\n        \"image_name\": build_result[\"image_name\"],\n        \"image_id\": build_result[\"image_id\"],\n        \"image_size\": build_result[\"image_size\"],\n        \"build_time\": build_result[\"build_time\"],\n        \"tag\": tag,\n    }\n    \n    self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n```\n\n### Rollback Pattern\n\n```python\ndef build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Full build with rollback:\n    \"\"\"\n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n    original_version = metadata.version\n    \n    self._validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n    \n    new_tag = self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n    \n    try:\n        if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n            result = self._build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n        else:\n            result = self._build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n        \n        self._update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, result, new_tag)\n        return result\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        # Rollback version\n        metadata.version = original_version\n        self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}. Version rolled back to {original_version}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- cli-toolkit/design.md — Overall CLI toolkit architecture\n- cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (Requirement: `build` command)\n- Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n- Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n- Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n- semver Python: https://python-semver.readthedocs.io/\n- AR-020 — CLI pack command (prerequisite, generates Dockerfile)\n- AR-022 — CLI publish command (follows build, uses image info)"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md","time":{"start":1775870238121,"end":1775870238167}}}}
